<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>hello</title>
</head>
<body>
<script type="text/javascript">
	function newChange(){
		var selectedId = document.getElementById('selectedId');
		var selectedValue = selectedId.options[selectedId.selectedIndex].value;
		if (selectedValue==0){
			document.body.bgColor='white';
		}
		else if (selectedValue==1)
		{
			document.body.bgColor='red';
		}
		else if (selectedValue==2){
			document.body.bgColor='green';
		}
		else if(selectedValue==3){
			document.body.bgColor='blue';
		}
		else{
			alert("select the given colors only!!!!!");
		}
	}
</script>
Select  the color of background you wanted from the following dropdown menu:-<br/>
<select id="selectedId" onchange="newChange()">
	<option value=0> White </option>
	<option value=1> Red </option>
	<option value=2> Green </option>
	<option value=3> Blue </option>
</select>
</body>
</html>
